# Goals

---

## Editor-G1 AutoDown Editor provides WYSIWYG block-based editing with Markdown/AutoDown serialization for Wiki and Spec content
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** Wiki-G1

- [ ] Block-based WYSIWYG editor replaces split-pane Markdown editor
- [ ] Native Markdown parse/serialize via Tiptap with bidirectional sync
- [ ] Slash commands, bubble menu, and drag handle for Notion-like UX
- [ ] Custom blocks render as Vue components via Tiptap node views
- [ ] AutoDown extensions: callouts, math, mermaid diagrams, spec references
- [ ] Used for Wiki content editing initially; extendable to Spec sections

AutoDown Editor is a Tiptap-based rich text editor that presents Markdown content as editable blocks. Each paragraph, heading, list, code block, and custom element is a distinct block with interactive Vue rendering. The editor serializes to clean Markdown for backend persistence and extends to AutoDown syntax for project-specific block types.
---

## Editor-G2 Phase 1 — Markdown WYSIWYG Editor
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** Editor-G1

- [ ] Tiptap editor core integrated into frontend with Vue 3 composition API
- [ ] StarterKit blocks: paragraph, heading, list, code block, blockquote, HR, image, link, table, task list
- [ ] Slash command palette for block insertion via "/"
- [ ] Bubble menu for inline formatting on text selection
- [ ] Drag handle for block reordering
- [ ] Replaces `MarkdownEditor.vue` in Wiki and Spec views
- [ ] Markdown round-trip: load from string, save to string, no data loss
---

## Editor-G3 Phase 2 — AutoDown Extensions
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** Editor-G2

- [ ] Callout block with info/warning/tip/danger types
- [ ] Math block with KaTeX rendering
- [ ] Mermaid diagram block with live rendering
- [ ] Spec reference block (`[[AgentConfig-G1]]`) with clickable links
- [ ] Custom `marked` tokenizers for each AutoDown syntax extension
- [ ] Each extension is a self-contained pair: Tiptap Node + Vue component
---

## Editor-G4 Phase 3 — Advanced Editing Features
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** Editor-G3

- [ ] Multi-column layout blocks
- [ ] Real-time collaborative cursors (Yjs integration)
- [ ] AI-assisted inline completion
- [ ] Version diff view between two document states
